caused reevaluation of the stance. I personally disagree that helms should be hide able, but that is my opinion too.<br><br>Sometimes it takes a while for a company to get it right. They experimented with LDoN and though it was a great start of an idea it didn't get it right. With DoN the idea was carried further and done better. We now have tasks, monster missions, and a better system for gaining rewards through adventure style points. Hurk’s point that it will take time to rebalance points is valid. If they remake LDoN point system like DoN it will definitely take a while. Perhaps they already have something in the works.<br><br>We have to consider that some things take much more time to code than others. My own experience proves this. Creating a toggle to hide helms is probably like 2 or 3 man hours of work at most. Redoing LDoNs point system is going to take much much longer. Probably a couple man months, though I am purely speculating.
