			You don't have to go all the way to the limit...<br><br><b>Tradable LDON points</b><br>They could go all the way and allow you to trade every kind of LDoN points.  Someone with high standing at butcherblock could then convert those points to tokens and sell them to someone else who would turn them in and immediately have high standing with butcherblock.<br><br>OR They could make one kind of points, which are camp neutral and do nothing to change your standing with any camp.  You still have to build your reputation with the camp to get access to powerful items, but once you do, you can buy enough points from another player to buy and entire suit of 1400 pt armor.<br><br><b>Reduce the Need to Build Reputation</b><br>A lot of folks want to be able to spend thier points at any camp even if they've never done a single adventure for that camp.  That's the extreme case.<br><br>The adventure points don't have to match up exactly with the reputation.<br><br>They could double the current reputation counters.  And make your reputation go up 2 points with the camp for every adventure point you earn.  You could get 30 points adventuring in Butcherblock and build 60 reputation there.  Then do 30 points in Guk and spend all 60 points on an item in Butcherblock.  This allows some flexibility while still encouraging people to see some of the out-of-the-way camps.
