		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Ldon is being looks at as a low to mid level&nbsp; enviroment.&nbsp; one dev specifically said&nbsp; they were gonna&nbsp; increase the point system for those levels.</DIV>
<DIV>with everyone wantng solo content. assiging&nbsp; ldon point for task completeions seems a viable route to&nbsp; give the soloers a bonus without lessening the desire for groups.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>setting up the equipment augs similiar to the way most ogf the wepon augs are useable on non ldon gear would&nbsp; attract some of the higher levels.</DIV>
<DIV>I dont think the point would be to make&nbsp; Ldon the thing to do again. I think the goal would be to make it more viable.</DIV>
<DIV>first thing to do would be to take away the 10 win&nbsp; a zone for point interchanebility.&nbsp; 25 total wind collectively would be far more reasonable than the current fifty. With all the options out there ldon should lighten up on a system they did away with in the don and dodh missions. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Increasing points awarded or lowering cost of equipment would certainly&nbsp; place new value on&nbsp; things you can acquire in ldon's&nbsp; and make them more attainable at a viable level.</DIV>
<DIV>Perhaps classses could actually get spells when&nbsp; they are most useful again.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As far as the high levels go..... you can make a case well thi stuff is mostly for lower levels. but they did make them doable b the post 65 so they might as well&nbsp;&nbsp; give them a bone</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I would think&nbsp; having the lavastorm camp&nbsp;&nbsp; accepting point in trae for haning out crystals would be a viable solution... of course with ldons being easier than dons&nbsp; they would have to assess a point value per crystal.&nbsp;and at a value that would make it still be more worthwhile to do the don missions </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
