Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=136573#M136573">40</a> of 75
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 256 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
skaal wrote:<BR>
<DIV>Given that Zajeer specifically mentioned looking at LDoN for the 20-50 range, (as they think 50+ is fine since they can do DoN), I don't expect a 65 or 70 will see much difference.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>That said, what I would like to see...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>(1) Point change.&nbsp; Either increase the points per mission, or decrease the point cost per item.&nbsp; The former is presumably much easier than the latter.&nbsp; Pretty much a no-brainer, and definitely what Zajeer is looking at, at least for the sub-50 crowd.&nbsp; (Getting only 51 for a 63 adventure, or 105 for a 63 hard/68 adventure is poor, but not nearly so bad as the point awards pre-50).</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>(2) Do away with, at minimum, type 3 slots and augments.&nbsp; Change the slots on the LDoN armour to type 1/7, 2, 9.&nbsp; Change all type 3 augs sold in LDoN to be type 9/12.&nbsp; Doing this prolongs the usefulness of both, allowing, for example, someone to get the 1492 breastplate, progress to DoNs, and get a type 9 aug from DoN for it.&nbsp; (You can do away with type 2 slots/augs too, but I'm not sure what you would change it to... 7?)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>Really like your ideas for the augs/aug slots!&nbsp; That would be great!</P>
<P>Another thing I would like to mention is the comparative cost of different pieces.&nbsp; I just don't see why all pieces of the current 1492 armor cost the same.&nbsp; Generally, a breastplate costs more than a bracer, ang gives more HP/Mana etc.&nbsp; The LDoN armor stats are this way, yet one bracer costs as much as a breastplate.&nbsp; The cost of a bracer should be considerably less than the cost of a breastplate.&nbsp; If the cost of the smaller items was less than the cost of the larger items within the same set, it would be possible for players to start collecting and using pieces of their armor set sooner, by starting with the smaller pieces first and working their way up to the larger pieces as they level up and get more points.</P>
<P>Two bracers still do not quite equal the stats of the breastplate, yet two bracers cost twice as much as the breastplate.&nbsp; If the price was scaled, it would be something more like this:&nbsp; Bracer-500, Gauntlets-750, Boots-750, Sleeves-850, Greaves-1050, Breastplate-1492.&nbsp; With points awarded at least at one per character level, a level 20 would get 20 points for one successful mission.&nbsp; At the current experience level, would be lvl 21 after two missions and would have 40 points. By 22, would have accumulated 82 points.&nbsp; (lvl 23, 128 points) (24, 176) (25, 226) (26, 278) (27, 332) (28, 386) (29, 444) (30, 504).&nbsp; So, using this model, a player could get the first piece of their best quality LDoN gear--one bracer--by Lvl 30 or so.&nbsp; Now I'm just using this as an example, and I do not know exactly what the numbers should be--but certainly it should not be less than one point per level at level 20, and perhaps scaling upward as well, to 1.5 points per level at 30, 2.0 at 40, etc.</P>
<P>I think being able to get a piece of the gear all along would help people to keep trying for the full set, rather than giving up because they can't see any reward for such a long time.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>Nodyin_Dev wrote: {SNIP}The ZEM (Zone Experience Modifier) on that zone [Paludal Caverns]is currently well below what you'll find in the hot zones (to the tune of 50% in some cases).  In fact the average hitpoint level in Paludal is higher than the zone I have picked out for the level 20 crowd.  I can't see any way that you wouldn't be better served hitting the new hotspots than Paludal when you hit the appropriate level ranges.
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
